  "local_port": 60558,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best spell and trap cards in Yu-Gi-Oh?",
  "response": "Yu-Gi-Oh! has a vast array of Spell and Trap cards, and their effectiveness often depends on the deck you're playing and the current meta. However, some cards are widely regarded as powerful and versatile across various strategies. Here are some of the best Spell and Trap cards in the game, categorized by their type:\n\n---\n\n### **Spell Cards**  \n1. **Monster Reborn**  \n   - Revives any monster from either player's Graveyard. It's a classic card that has been a staple in many decks for years.  \n\n2. **Raigeki**  \n   - Destroys all monsters your opponent controls. A devastating board wipe that can turn the tide of a duel.  \n\n3. **Harpie's Feather Duster**  \n   - Destroys all Spells and Traps your opponent controls. Essential for breaking through backrow-heavy decks.  \n\n4. **Pot of Prosperity**  \n   - Allows you to excavate cards from your Deck and add one to your hand, at the cost of banishing cards face-down. A great consistency booster for many decks.  \n\n5. **Called by the Grave**  \n   - Banishes a monster in the opponent's Graveyard and negates effects of cards with the same name. A crucial hand trap counter.  \n\n6. **Dark Ruler**  \n   - Negates the effects of all face-up monsters your opponent controls and prevents you from taking battle damage this turn. Great for breaking established boards.  \n\n7. **Foolish Burial**  \n   - Sends any monster from your Deck to the Graveyard. Synergizes well with decks that rely on Gy effects.  \n\n8. **Lightning Storm**  \n   - Destroys either all Spells/Traps or all Attack Position monsters your opponent controls. A versatile board breaker.\n\n---\n\n### **Trap Cards**  \n1. **Solemn Judgment**  \n   - Negates any Summon or Spell/Trap activation at the cost of halving your LP. A powerful counter to almost anything.  \n\n2. **Infinite Impermanence**  \n   - Negates a monster's effects and prevents them from activating in the same column. Also works as a hand trap.  \n\n3. **Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring** (Technically a hand trap, but often used as a Trap-like effect)  \n   - Negates effects that search, draw, or send cards from Deck to Gy.  \n\n4. **Evenly Matched**  \n   - Forces your opponent to banish cards from their field face-down at the end of the Battle Phase. A great way to clear an opponent's board.  \n\n5. **Torrential Tribute**  \n   - Destroys all monsters on the field when a monster is Summoned. A classic board wipe.  \n\n6. **Gozen Match**  \n   - Restricts both players to controlling only one Attribute of monsters. Great for disrupting certain strategies.  \n\n7. **Rivalry of Warlords**  \n   - Restricts both players to controlling only one Type of monster. Another strong floodgate.  \n\n8. **Ice Dragon's Prison**  \n   - Targets and banishes monsters from both players' fields or Gy. Versatile removal.\n\n---\n\n### **Honorable Mentions**  \n- **Forbidden Droplet**: Negates monster effects and halves their ATK.  \n- **Crossout Designator**: Counters specific cards in your opponent's Deck.  \n- **Super Polymerization**: Fuses using monsters from either side of the field.  \n\n---\n\nThese cards are considered some of the best due to their versatility, impact on the game state, and ability to fit into a wide range of strategies. However, always consider your deck's synergy and the meta when building your Spell/Trap lineup!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
